title: Google\Cloud\Orchestration\Airflow\Service\V1\PrivateEnvironmentConfig
name: PrivateEnvironmentConfig
description:
The configuration information for configuring a Private IP Cloud Composer environment.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.orchestration.airflow.service.v1.PrivateEnvironmentConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.enable_private_environment
params.description: Optional. If true, a Private IP Cloud Composer environment is created. If this field is set to true, IPAllocationPolicy.use_ip_aliases must be set to true.

params.name: data.private_cluster_config
params.description: Optional. Configuration for the private GKE cluster for a Private IP Cloud Composer environment.

params.name: data.web_server_ipv4_cidr_block
params.description: Optional. The CIDR block from which IP range for web server will be reserved. Needs to be disjoint from private_cluster_config.master_ipv4_cidr_block and cloud_sql_ipv4_cidr_block.

params.name: data.cloud_sql_ipv4_cidr_block
params.description: Optional. The CIDR block from which IP range in tenant project will be reserved for Cloud SQL. Needs to be disjoint from web_server_ipv4_cidr_block.

params.name: data.web_server_ipv4_reserved_range
params.description: Output only. The IP range reserved for the tenant project's App Engine VMs.
